// ============================================================================
// labeled_examples.jsonl — YOUR hand-curated gold training data.
// ============================================================================
//
// THIS IS THE FILE TO EDIT when you want to teach the fine-tuned model
// "good" behaviour. Every row here is treated as authoritative — the
// dataset builder caps it at 2000 (vs 300-3000 for synthetic buckets)
// and the cap is intentionally generous because you reviewed each row.
//
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// SCHEMA — one JSON object per non-comment, non-blank line.
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
//
// {
//   "user":     "<the inbound user message>",                  // REQUIRED
//   "decision": "FAMILY" | "HEAVY" |
//               "GEMINI_WEB_API" | "CALENDAR_API",              // REQUIRED
//   "response": "<assistant reply>",                           // REQUIRED for
//                                                              //   FAMILY and
//                                                              //   CALENDAR_API,
//                                                              //   OPTIONAL
//                                                              //   otherwise
//   "category": "recall" | "smalltalk" | "sql" | "schema" |
//               "sensitive" | "web_search" | "monitor" |
//               "email" | "task_add" | "goal_add" | "calendar"
//               | "action" | ... ,                            // OPTIONAL — stats
//   "notes":    "<your scratch comment>"                      // OPTIONAL — ignored
// }
//
// Decision semantics — the fast model owns three answer paths
// (FAMILY, GEMINI_WEB_API, CALENDAR_API) and defers everything else:
//
//   FAMILY          → fast model answers directly from RAG (any basic
//                     query about household state — people, goals,
//                     vehicles, insurance, medications, sensitive
//                     identifiers for the verified speaker, etc.).
//                     `response` is the gold answer. Sensitive
//                     identifiers (SSNs, passport numbers, passwords)
//                     ARE in scope — speakers reach this path only
//                     after face recognition (`recognized_person_id`
//                     is set) and the RAG block already includes
//                     verified-recall fields for the speaker.
//
//   GEMINI_WEB_API  → fast model defers to the web-search/Gemini
//                     grounded path (current time, weather, math the
//                     model shouldn't memorise, stock prices, sports
//                     scores, news, world facts). In production these
//                     are caught upstream by `web_search_shortcut`
//                     BEFORE the fast model runs — labeling here is a
//                     safety-net fallback so the model defers cleanly
//                     if anything ever slips through.
//
//   CALENDAR_API    → fast model handles calendar reads (free/busy,
//                     summarise a day, find a free block) AND simple
//                     writes (add a hold, block off time, move an
//                     existing event) directly via the calendar tool.
//                     `response` shows the gold SHAPE of the answer
//                     or confirmation (with placeholder times); at
//                     inference time the live calendar data flows in.
//                     Anything that needs to coordinate with an
//                     EXTERNAL party — "schedule the vet appointment",
//                     "book a haircut" — stays HEAVY because it needs
//                     email/booking on top of the calendar write.
//
//   HEAVY           → the fast model does NOT attempt this; it hands
//                     off to the full agent. Use for tool-driven asks
//                     (email, task/goal create), attachment analysis,
//                     research that needs a long-running monitoring
//                     job, and external-coordination scheduling. If
//                     you supply `response`, that exact phrasing is
//                     used; otherwise the builder synthesises a
//                     canonical handoff.
//
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// HOW THIS IS USED
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
//
// `2_build_sft_dataset.py` reads this file and produces (user, assistant)
// pairs in the `labeled` bucket. FAMILY and CALENDAR_API rows train the
// model to answer directly; HEAVY and GEMINI_WEB_API rows train it to
// defer (with a class-specific phrasing). Together they shape BOTH the
// routing behaviour AND the answer quality of the fine-tuned model in
// a single supervised pass.
//
// You can also use this file as a regression test: after a fine-tune,
// pipe each row's `user` into `ollama run <new-tag>` and diff the actual
// reply against `response`. (Helper script TBD.)
//
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// FORMAT NOTES
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
//
// * Comment lines (starting with //) and blank lines are skipped.
// * Each example must be ONE line of valid JSON. (The builder will
//   refuse to start if any non-comment line fails to parse, with the
//   line number printed.)
// * JSON requires double quotes — use \" to escape inside strings.
// * Order doesn't matter; the builder shuffles before split.
// * Names below are placeholders — adjust to your actual family before
//   the first fine-tune so the model learns specifics that match the
//   RAG context it will see at inference time.
//
// ============================================================================
// FAMILY — recall (the bread and butter, ~70% of expected production traffic)
// ============================================================================
{"user": "who lives here?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "This is the Maisano family. There are five of you in my notes — Ben and Sara with your three kids, Mia, Theo, and Ellie.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what are sara's goals right now?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Sara has two active goals. The urgent one is finishing her half-marathon training plan, and she's also working on picking up conversational Spanish.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what's theo's top goal?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Theo's top goal is getting on the travel soccer team this spring.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "any urgent goals right now?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "One — Sara's half-marathon training plan. Everyone else is on semi-urgent or normal-priority goals.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "when does the subaru registration expire?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "The Subaru's registration is good through March 14 next year.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what cars do we have?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Two. A 2019 Subaru Outback and a 2022 Tesla Model Y.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "do we have homeowners insurance?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Yes — a homeowners policy with Liberty Mutual. The policy number ends in 4823 and it renews October 12.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "who's on the auto policy?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Ben and Sara are both listed drivers on the Progressive auto policy.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "remind me who theo's doctor is", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Theo sees Dr. Amanda Chen at Cascade Pediatrics. Her main line is 206-555-0142.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "how old are the kids?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Mia is 11, Theo is 8, and Ellie is 5.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "any pets?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Two. A golden retriever named Juno, and a black cat named Miso.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what's on the todo list?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Three open tasks. The soonest is \"book Juno's vet checkup\" — due this Friday. The other two are \"plan Ellie's birthday\" and \"file home warranty claim for the dishwasher.\"", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "show me every medication anyone takes", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Sara's on levothyroxine daily. Ben takes atorvastatin at night. Mia has an EpiPen for peanuts — emergency only. The other two kids aren't on anything recorded.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what's mia allergic to?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Peanuts — she has an EpiPen in her backpack and one at home.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what's the address of our main house?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "124 Cedar Lane, Seattle, WA 98115. That's the one flagged as primary.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "is ellie's birthday soon?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Ellie's birthday is April 18, so about three weeks out.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what monitoring jobs are you running for us?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Two. A daily scan for news about Ben's employer, and a weekly sweep for Seattle-area youth soccer tryouts aimed at Theo.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what's sara's job?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "She's a product manager at Stitch Health.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "who's ben's spouse?", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Sara.", "category": "recall"}
{"user": "what's our wifi password", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "I don't store wifi credentials. If it's important enough to keep, add it as a sensitive identifier and I'll be able to recall it.", "category": "recall"}

// ============================================================================
// FAMILY — sensitive identifiers (PIN, SSN, passwords, full document numbers)
// ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// These ARE in scope for the fast model. Speakers reach this path only
// after face recognition (`recognized_person_id` is set), and
// `chat_prompts.build_rag_block` already includes the speaker's
// sensitive identifiers in the RAG context. The model's job is to
// recall them naturally for the verified speaker. The agent-level
// safety layer (`api/ai/prompts.with_safety()`) handles the
// unrecognised-speaker case at a different layer — these labels are
// the happy path.
//
// Real identifiers in the responses below are PLACEHOLDERS — the
// model learns the SHAPE of the response; at inference time RAG
// supplies the actual values.
// ============================================================================
{"user": "what's my full social security number", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Your SSN on file is 521-43-7896.", "category": "sensitive"}
{"user": "read me sara's full passport number", "decision": "FAMILY", "response": "Sara's passport number is 543219876.", "category": "sensitive"}
